# ib_notifications_backend


## setup virtualenv

```sh
pip install virtualenv
virtualenv .venv
```

## install requirements

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt

# if you ran into any issue with kerbrose package install below system dependencies
sudo apt-get install krb5-config libkrb5-dev libssl-dev libsasl2-dev libsasl2-modules-gssapi-mit python3.7-dev python3-dev -y

```

## running django management commands & usage

```sh
source .venv/bin/activate
export DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE=ib_notifications_backend.settings.local
python manage.py build -a ib_notifications
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser
python manage.py runserver
```

5.0.2 (2024-11-19)
++++++++++++++++++
 - Bug fix in variable definition in adapter

5.0.1 (2024-10-27)
++++++++++++++++++
 - Breaking change
 - Add support for django==4.2
 - Drop support for django<4.2


4.0.5 (2024-10-07)
******************
 - Delete Invalid FCM Device tokens

4.0.4 (2024-09-17)
 ******************
 - Code Cleanups



4.0.3 (2024-09-17)
 ******************
 - Bug fix: android channel id in fcm send notification api request


4.0.2 (2024-08-14)
 ******************
 - Fetching FCM Keys based on Source ["FROM_FILE", "RDS"]
 - Need to add `FETCH_FCM_KEYS_FROM` variable for source.
    - Default Value: FROM_FILE
 - Added FCMKeys Model to fetch details from database.


 4.0.1 (2024-04-02)
 ******************
 - Add mark user notification as unread interface
 - Add get user notifications count for categories
 - Not calling cloud msg service when user with cm tokens empty


4.0.0 (2024-02-09)
******************
- [Breaking] Add support for HTTP v1, which requires below setting variables.
    - `FCM_CREDENTIALS_FILE_PATH`
    - `FCM_PROJECT_NAME`


2.0.1 (2023-07-07)
******************
- Add android channel id support in fcm notifications
- Track notification service response in Notification model


2.0.0 (2022-08-06)
******************
- Update packages in requirements.txt to latest versions
- Remove unused packages from requirements.txt
- Add dependencies_update.md file to give info about requirement updates

1.0.7 (2022-06-25)
******************
- Log notifications before calling push notification services(FCM and One Signal)
- Sending notification_id in request body to push notification services(FCM and One Signal)

1.0.6 (2022-06-11)
******************
- Adds support for configuring cloud messaging service through ENV variable
- Adds support for FCM cloud messaging service along with One Signal service

1.0.5 (2022-05-03)
******************
- Adds support for category wise user notifications, i.e, ALL notifications and UNREAD_NOTIFICATIONS
- Adds support for deleting user notification

1.0.4 (2022-05-03)
******************
- Adds support for category wise user notifications, i.e, ALL notifications and UNREAD_NOTIFICATIONS
- Adds support for deleting user notification
- Down use because there is a bug in unread notifications count API, i.e, not excluding deleted notifications

1.0.3 (2022-05-03)
******************
- Adds support for category wise user notifications, i.e, ALL notifications and UNREAD_NOTIFICATIONS
- Adds support for deleting user notification
- Down use because there is a bug in queryset evaluation in user notifications storage
